1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,242
Use delegation mode when the outcome is specific, the steps can be executed with available tools, and success can be checked.

2
00:00:07,192 --> 00:00:12,076
The human defines the task package; the agent runs the work and returns evidence.

3
00:00:12,076 --> 00:00:22,673
A useful delegation packet has six parts: the desired outcome, the relevant context, hard constraints, allowed tools, stop conditions, and the evidence required at handoff.

4
00:00:22,673 --> 00:00:26,182
Missing any one of these creates hidden interpretation work.

5
00:00:26,182 --> 00:00:29,307
Give the agent authority that matches the consequence.

6
00:00:29,307 --> 00:00:33,884
Reading files, drafting a report, or running tests may be reversible.

7
00:00:33,884 --> 00:00:39,269
Publishing, spending money, deleting data, or messaging people needs explicit gates.

8
00:00:39,269 --> 00:00:42,875
Autonomy is scoped permission, not a personality trait.

9
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:45,144
Require observable evidence.

10
00:00:45,144 --> 00:00:48,903
A code task returns the changed files and test results.

11
00:00:48,903 --> 00:00:53,317
A research task returns primary sources and unresolved uncertainty.

12
00:00:53,317 --> 00:00:58,663
A publishing task returns the public URL, visibility state, and channel placement.

13
00:00:58,663 --> 00:01:02,423
The common failure is reviewing the narration instead of the result.

14
00:01:02,423 --> 00:01:06,163
An agent can sound confident while the artifact is incomplete.

15
00:01:06,163 --> 00:01:10,048
Inspect the output, the checks, and the boundary conditions.

16
00:01:10,048 --> 00:01:12,182
Confidence is not evidence.

17
00:01:12,182 --> 00:01:16,384
Delegation ends with acceptance, rejection, or a mode switch.

18
00:01:16,384 --> 00:01:21,298
If the agent finds an ambiguous requirement, bring the task back to collaboration.

19
00:01:21,298 --> 00:01:24,855
If it finds an unknown problem, move to exploration.

20
00:01:24,855 --> 00:01:27,451
A good stop is part of a good handoff.

21
00:01:27,451 --> 00:01:30,942
First, Delegate only a specified task package.

22
00:01:30,942 --> 00:01:35,884
Second, Give tools, constraints, stop conditions, and evidence.

23
00:01:35,884 --> 00:01:39,557
Third, Review the outcome, not the agent's confidence.
